 Background                                                         72 1451     
 ----------                                                         72 1451     
                                                                    72 1451     
 This library was produced by the Low Energy Interaction Physics    72 1451     
 (LEIP) group at NC State University. The inelastic scattering      72 1451     
 thermal scattering law data for Uranium Mononitride (UN) were      72 1451     
 developed using ab initio lattice dynamics methods [1]. The        72 1451     
 LEAPR module from the NJOY code system was used to produce MF=7    72 1451     
 MT=2 and 4 for U in UN. Modifications to the LEAPR module were     72 1451     
 made to calculate the coherent elastic cross-section for UN [2].   72 1451     
 N-14 has an incoherent nuclear cross section of 0.5 barns [3];     72 1451     
 therefore, to capture both coherent and incoherent elastic         72 1451     
 scattering, the entire coherent elastic cross section data         72 1451     
 (MF=7, MT=2) for UN is tabulated in the present U in UN library.   72 1451     
 The bound coherent cross section of nitrogen in this evaluation    72 1451     
 is 10.8907 barns based on the current ENDF-VII.1 N-14 library.     72 1451     
                                                                    72 1451     
